text: Mika Yamauchi (山内 美加 Yamauchi Mika, born October 7, 1969) is a former volleyball player from Japan, who was a member of the Japan Women's National Team. Her nickname is Mika (ミカ). ==Profile== *Birthplace: Yurihonjo, Akita *Height: 182 cm ==National team== *1992: 5th place in the Olympic Games of BarcelonaOlympic results *1993: 4th place in the Grand Champions Cup *1994: 7th place in the World Championship *1995: 6th place in the World Cup *1996: 9th place in the Olympic Games of Atlanta ==References== Category:Olympic volleyball players of Japan Category:Volleyball players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Volleyball players at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Japanese women's volleyball players Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:Asian Games medalists in volleyball Category:Volleyball players at the 1994 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 1994 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Japan
